\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}2. Core Technology Stack & Architectural Strategy\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl300\slmult1\partightenfactor0
\ls12\ilvl0
\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}The application architecture uses a mobile\uc0\u8209 first, decoupled tech stack optimized for swift solo\u8209 operator velocity, high operational resilience, and seamless integration with the spec\u8209 driven process outlined in Section 1, above.\
\pard\tx240\tx960\pardeftab720\li960\fi-360\ri0\sl300\slmult1\partightenfactor0
\ls13\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}\uc0\u9679 	
\f1\b Process & Lifecycle Engine: 
\f0\b0 GitHub SpecKit (via specify\uc0\u8209 cli) to parse specifications and orchestrate repeatable development loops, ensuring that every change is anchored in the documented Hierarchy of Truth.\
{\listtext	\'95	}\uc0\u9679 	
\f1\b Development IDE: 
\f0\b0 Cursor with advanced language models (e.g., Claude\uc0\u8209 3.5\u8209 Sonnet) to provide AI pairing that operates directly against the repository artifacts (constitution, glossary, specs, plans) instead of ad\u8209 hoc prompts\
{\listtext	\'95	}\uc0\u9679 	
\f1\b Client Application Framework: 
\f0\b0 Native iOS development (Swift / SwiftUI) to leverage platform\uc0\u8209 native accessibility, performance, and offline behaviors critical for multi\u8209 generational, real\u8209 world property management.\
{\listtext	\'95	}\uc0\u9679 	
\f1\b Backend & Database Layer: 
\f0\b0 Supabase with PostgreSQL, built\uc0\u8209 in authentication, and real\u8209 time sync to support strongly typed data models, household\u8209 scoped access control, and low\u8209 latency state sharing across family members.\
{\listtext	\'95	}\uc0\u9679 	
\f1\b Visual Management & Deployment: 
\f0\b0 GitHub Projects for automated Kanban and GitHub Actions to continuously build and ship iOS binaries to TestFlight, for a single, source\uc0\u8209 controlled path from specification to testable artifacts on physical devices.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sb320\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls13\ilvl0
\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}3. Operational Lifecycle & Platform Readiness Plan\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl300\slmult1\partightenfactor0
\ls13\ilvl0
\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}Transitioning from an early prototype to a production system capable of reliably supporting remote property management requires strict enforcement of the operational lifecycle:\
\pard\tx240\tx960\pardeftab720\li960\fi-360\ri0\sl300\slmult1\partightenfactor0
\ls14\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	1.	}1.	
\f1\b Database Schema Evolution:
\f0\b0  Integration of Supabase Migrations into the GitHub pipeline. Database alterations must be handled through deterministic version-controlled migration scripts rather than manual dashboard editing, protecting live user data and property task history.\
{\listtext	2.	}2.	
\f1\b Secrets and DevSecOps Management:
\f0\b0  Exclusion of raw API keys or infrastructure credentials from source code. Secure environment variables or cloud secrets managers will inject configuration values securely at compile time or runtime.\
{\listtext	3.	}3.	
\f1\b Observability & Remote Telemetry:
\f0\b0  Integration of mobile-side crash telemetry and real-time log aggregation (e.g., Sentry for iOS). This ensures offline application errors or synchronization failures in low-connectivity situations are queued and transmitted for remote diagnostics immediately upon signal recovery.\
{\listtext	4.	}4.	
\f1\b Eval-Driven Regression Prevention:
\f0\b0  Construction of standard evaluation data sets representing core application scenarios (such as shared task state transitions and cross-user notifications). These run during the automated pipeline execution to guarantee that new code never introduces regressive synchronization errors.\
}